text: b"Thanks for all your support and business! 2 years until @Square is 10, and we're excited to share what we've been up to!"

name: jack
text: b'New markets: we aspire to be a global service. But doing that with payments is slow going. Team is working to move faster'

name: jack
text: b"Loyalty: we've tested a lot here and haven't found the right answer for all. Still working on this. Think we're now closer"

name: jack
text: b'API: we are working hard this year to open more of our services up to developers!'

name: jack
text: b"Bitcoin: we tried this with our ecommerce store years back. Didn't see much. Would love to see a digital currency thrive"

name: jack
text: b'And thanks for all the @Square feedback yesterday!  Asks we heard: bitcoin, API, loyalties, and more markets. https://t.co/pjFTn74d5d'

name: jack
text: b'We will be more open. Thanks for all your support and patience as we plan for the next 10 years of our service. And thanks to @bchesky!'

name: jack
text: b"The open exchange of information has a positive impact on the world, and that's why we're here. That starts with an open dialogue with you."

name: jack
text: b"We'll consider everything we heard from you. Not going to ship all of it, but will be more transparent about why and what we learned"

name: jack
text: b"Conversations: this is a big part of the magic of Twitter and currently really difficult to follow & manage. We'll work to make this easier"

name: jack
text: b'Topics: lots here but simply being able to follow topics was strongest request. Being more topic/interest-focused (v account) opens up a lot'

name: jack
text: b'Edit: clearest ask was to provide a quick way to fix errors. Anything beyond requires showing edit history given tweets are public record'

name: jack
text: b'Abuse: obviously a ton of work ahead but biggest ask was for greater transparency around our actions (or inaction) and faster shipping'
